Bheki Cele updates us on the readiness of the police ahead of the elections. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister, Bheki Cele, says its all systems go for election 2019. Cele says the South African National Defence Force will be deployed to certain areas in KwaZulu-Natal and the North West. READ: Slow start to special voting KZN has seen numerous political killings while in the North West residents are threatening to protest on election day. Cele says law enforcement agencies are on standby in all other provinces should they be needed.